Death has occurred in Benin City, Edo State, of retired Major Matthew Igbinakenzua Omorogbe, the father of the Resident Electoral Commissioner for Bayelsa State, Dr Cyril A. Omorogbe. He passed on at the ripe age of 88, on Wednesday, 31st March 2021. Late Major Omorogbe was a former Director of the Nigerian Army Physical Training school, Zaria, Kaduna State in the 1970s. Until his death, Major Omorogbe was an ex-officio of RANAO, a body of retired Nigerian Army officers, an ardent sports enthusiast particularly as a squash player and shooting where he chaired Edo State Shooting Association. He is survived by children, grandchildren led by the eldest, Dr Cyril Omorogbe, Resident Electoral Commissioner Bayelsa State. A statement by the family explained that the funeral programme shall be made public in due course. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state.  INEC resident commissioner in Bayelsa loses father Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…INEC resident commissioner in Bayelsa loses father [ICYMI] Lekki Shootings: Why We Lied About Our Presence — General Taiwo The Lagos State Judicial Panel of Inquiry probing the killings at Lekki Toll Gate, on Saturday resumed viewing of the 24hrs footage of the October 20, 2020 shooting of #End